Universal Beijing Resort (UBR) will reopen on June 15 under strict compliance with epidemic prevention and control policies and requirements, according to an announcement released on its official website. According to the announcement, The Universal Studio Grand Hotel, UNO Hotel and Universal CityWalk Beijing will open to the guests one day ahead on June 14, with a 75 percent capacity limit. Indoor attractions and entertainment will also have the capacity limit. All guests are required to provide a 72-hour negative NAT test result, to present their Health Kit and personal ID, to comply with a quick temperature check, as well as to provide a valid park reservation QR code before entering the park.